    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Customer Relationship Management Practices among Consumer Durable White Goods Customers in Chennai City</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Krishnan.A.R</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Customer Relationship<br />Consumer Durable</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Mar-2011 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">T0022</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Today ‘customer’ is the King in companies management with the
power to change their short/long term polices and strategies. Therefore,
enough knowledge of environment, expectation of customer and their desires
are very important to find the best solution for facing un-expected behaviors of
customer and then behave in such a manner to change the minds of customers
in the direction of company’s profit.
Organizations in order to be successful should look into the needs and
wants of their customer. That is the reason as to why many researchers and
academicians have continuously emphasized the importance of Customer
Relationship Management (CRM) in the form of increased customer
satisfaction and loyalty to improve the customer retention, ultimately
increasing profitability. This study follows the customer Satisfaction, Loyalty
and Retention (SLR) model.
Customer satisfaction is vital, as satisfaction influences repurchase
intentions, whereas dissatisfaction is seen as a primary reason for customer
defection or discontinuation of purchase. In line with this, consequences of
customer satisfaction and dissatisfaction must be considered. Customer
retention is a concept gaining more and more attention in today’s business
where a loyal customer is considered as an essential component to
vii
organizational success. Corporations strive to identify and manage effective
methods to retain their customers. Postulated theory also shows a positive
connection between customer satisfaction, loyalty and retention. Therefore,
the above mentioned are all very important for an organization to be
successful. However, not enough studies have been conducted on the subject
in the consumer durable white goods industry though some research papers
have been published globally. Hence a study of these relationships will prove
to be useful for the success of business.
Consumer durable white goods sector is adopting customer relationship
management as a strategy aimed at retaining the valuable customer and in
turn, to increase customer satisfaction and ultimately customer loyalty.
However, as more studies are being done on the outcome of CRM strategies
over time, it is becoming evident that the costs often outweigh the expected
benefits and CRM have consistently over promised or under delivered. Often,
customer satisfaction is increased slightly but loyalty rates do not increase at
all. Firms have focused on customer satisfaction rates largely because of the
suggestions, historically; there is a strong, positive relationship between
customer service and loyalty. This study is an investigation of the use of CRM
practices in the consumer durable white goods industry and its effect on
satisfaction and loyalty levels to the firm. This study is accomplished using
data from a customer survey conducted in the white goods in Chennai city.
Hypotheses are tested using chi square test and correlation. The results suggest
viii
that satisfaction does drive overall customer satisfaction and that, in turn,
overall customer satisfaction does drive loyalty. The customer loyalty does
drive retention. However demographic information does not have a significant
effect in determining overall customer satisfaction or loyalty rates</td></tr>
